<h1>@HI{{goro}}</h1>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<strong>@HI{{goro}}</strong> is used with a specific point in time to indicate an approximation around that point.
<p></p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{itsu<strong>goro</strong>@KJ{{north^capital}}ni@KJ{{going}}kimasuka.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Roughly when are you going to Beijing?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

<h2> Notes </h2>

<p>
Note that <strong>@HI{{goro}}</strong> is used with a specific point in time whereas <a href="grammar-particle-kurai.html">@HI{{kurai/gurai}}</a>
is used with a time interval.
</p>

